page.title: 09SILAGING,COTEHILL
page.content: My dad is silaging .He is cutting grass with a forage harvester. He is leading grass which means taking it to the silage pit. He will be finished in a week. He has a barrel on the front of his tractor with treacle in it.It is mixed into the silage. The cows love it.They put the grass in the silage pit. They put a sheet over. It is the cows feed for the winter and when they are milking they get cow cake. Then he will cut the straw and then he will mow it and turn it then bale it and put it in the barn.
